      "source_id": "fd43f41a-8f3b-40a2-8359-4be5c4682e07",
      "citation_number": 58,
      "cited_text": "Narrated 'Umar: One day the Prophet stood up amongst us for a long period and informed us about the beginning of creation (and talked about everything in detail) till he mentioned how the people of Paradise will enter their places and the people of Hell will enter their places. Some re-membered what he had said, and some forgot it.",
      "start_char": 1589734,
      "end_char": 1590068,
      "chunk_id": "9c3cbe6d-dab4-4db6-98fd-287a79f5f949"
    },
    {
      "source_id": "6e2aa952-2370-4153-9e9e-1fdc4d086a83",
      "citation_number": 59,
      "cited_text": "their sight. Every time it lights [the way] for them, they walk therein; but when darkness comes over them, they stand [still]. And if God had willed, He could have taken away their hearing and their sight. Indeed, God is over all things competent.",
      "start_char": 82075,
      "end_char": 82324,
      "chunk_id": "40f44ee3-9c5a-4733-96f8-a41c53cbced8"
